- Layer 3: 2 green cube blocks placed side by side on the yellow block
- Layer 4: 1 blue rectangular block placed on one green cube
- Layer 5 (Top): 1 orange triangular/roof piece on top of the blue block

## Spatial Relationships
- The red arches form the base with the connecting piece between them
- The yellow horizontal block sits on top of the red base, spanning its entire width
- Two identical green cubes sit side by side on the yellow block
- The blue rectangular block is positioned on top of the right green cube
- The orange triangular roof piece sits on top of the blue block
